text.tspan: Thank you for supporting TurboLEDz. Before you start assembly, please note
that components will be soldered on both sides of the PCB. The LED bars will
be mounted on the front (where the TurboLEDz logo is.) All the other com-
ponents will be mounted on the back (where there are pre-mounted SMD ICs.)
https://turboledz.com
Solder only 1 side of the micro-controller to the
header (pads RAW,GND,RST,VCC...10) at the top-
end of the header pins.
Use a temporary spacer to mount the controller
up high. (e.g. creditcards or cardboard to space.)
Solder the 12-pin header to the back of the
board (With the Vcc LAT CLK ACL IN.R IN.A IN.G
annotations.)
Make sure you insert the short end of the header
into the PCB, as the Controller goes on the far
end of the long side.
Mount the LED bars at the front of the PCB (side
with TurboLEDz logo.)
Before inserting, check for bent pins.
Solder all LED bars.
After soldering, clip all excess leads from the
ledbars.
I recommend a good quality flush cutter, as it is
quite a bit of work: 192 leads in total.
Solder the capacitor at C1 at the backside of the
PCB. It has no polarity, so orientation does not
matter.
Assembly Manual TurboLEDz 810c
Take note:
The PCB and Controller will be mated via one row
of 12 header pins.
They need to be spaced so that both boards don't
touch at the undersides.
This will be explained below.
